Question

Consider the parametric equations for \(0\le t\le2\pi\): \[x = \cos(5t)+\sin(6t)\] \[y = \sin(8t)+\cos(4t)\]

Find the matching graph.


Answerlist

  • A
  • B
  • C
  • D

Solution

You will want to use a graphing utility.

Desmos

To graph a parametric equation in Desmos, you can graph a set of points by writing \((x(t),\,y(t))\) and give boundaries on \(t\):

Write \(x(t)\) and \(y(t)\): \[(\cos(5t)+\sin(6t),\, \sin(8t)+\cos(4t))\]

Set the boundaries on \(t\): \[0\le t \le 2\pi\]

This will generate the correct graph:
